trans-unit.source: Azure Active Directory developer's guide | Microsoft Azure
trans-unit.target: Azure Active Directory developer's guide | Microsoft Azure

trans-unit.source: This article provides a comprehensive guide to developer-oriented resources for Azure Active Directory.
trans-unit.target: This article provides a comprehensive guide to developer-oriented resources for Azure Active Directory.

trans-unit.source: As an identity management as a service (IDMaaS) platform, Azure Active Directory provides developers an effective way to integrate identity management into their applications.
trans-unit.target: As an identity management as a service (IDMaaS) platform, Azure Active Directory provides developers an effective way to integrate identity management into their applications.

trans-unit.source: The following articles provide overviews on implementation and key features of Azure Active Directory.
trans-unit.target: The following articles provide overviews on implementation and key features of Azure Active Directory.

trans-unit.source: We suggest that you read them in order, or jump to <linkText>Getting started</linkText><title></title> if you're ready to dig in.
trans-unit.target: We suggest that you read them in order, or jump to <linkText>Getting started</linkText><title></title> if you're ready to dig in.

trans-unit.source: <linkText>Integrating with Azure Active Directory</linkText><title></title>: Discover why integration with Azure Active Directory offers the best solution for secure sign-in and authorization.
trans-unit.target: <linkText>Integrating with Azure Active Directory</linkText><title></title>: Discover why integration with Azure Active Directory offers the best solution for secure sign-in and authorization.

trans-unit.source: <linkText>Active Directory authentication scenarios</linkText><title></title>: Take advantage of simplified authentication in Azure Active Directory to provide sign-on to your application.
trans-unit.target: <linkText>Active Directory authentication scenarios</linkText><title></title>: Take advantage of simplified authentication in Azure Active Directory to provide sign-on to your application.

trans-unit.source: <linkText>Azure Active Directory Graph API</linkText><title></title>: Use the Azure Active Directory Graph API to programmatically access Azure Active Directory through REST API endpoints.
trans-unit.target: <linkText>Azure Active Directory Graph API</linkText><title></title>: Use the Azure Active Directory Graph API to programmatically access Azure Active Directory through REST API endpoints.

trans-unit.source: <linkText>Integrating applications in Azure Active Directory</linkText><title></title>: Learn about registering your application and the branding guidelines for multitenant applications.
trans-unit.target: <linkText>Integrating applications in Azure Active Directory</linkText><title></title>: Learn about registering your application and the branding guidelines for multitenant applications.

trans-unit.source: <linkText>Azure Active Directory authentication libraries</linkText><title></title>: Easily authenticate users to obtain access tokens by using the Azure authentication libraries.
trans-unit.target: <linkText>Azure Active Directory authentication libraries</linkText><title></title>: Easily authenticate users to obtain access tokens by using the Azure authentication libraries.

trans-unit.source: To view Azure Active Directory overviews presented at the Build 2015 conference, see the <linkText>Videos</linkText><title></title> section below.

trans-unit.target: <linkText>SAML 2.0 protocol reference</linkText><title></title>: The SAML 2.0 protocol enables applications to provide a single sign-on experience to their users.

trans-unit.source: <linkText>OAuth 2.0 protocol reference</linkText><title></title>: You can use the OAuth 2.0 protocol to authorize access to web applications and web APIs in your Azure Active Directory tenant.
trans-unit.target: <linkText>OAuth 2.0 protocol reference</linkText><title></title>: You can use the OAuth 2.0 protocol to authorize access to web applications and web APIs in your Azure Active Directory tenant.

trans-unit.target: <linkText>OpenID Connect 1.0 protocol reference</linkText><title></title>: The OpenID Connect 1.0 protocol extends OAuth 2.0 for use as an authentication protocol.

trans-unit.target: <linkText>WS-Federation 1.2 protocol reference</linkText><title></title>: The WS-Federation 1.2 protocol is specified in the Web Services Federation Version 1.2 Specification.
